Since there is no function to the left of the left-most x to tell APL what to do with the result, it simply outputs it to the display (on a single line, separated by spaces) without needing any explicit instruction to do that.
"?" also has a monadic equivalent called roll, which simply returns a single random integer between 1 and its sole operand o the right of i, inclusive. Thus, a role-playing game program might use the expression "?20" to roll a twenty-sided die.
